      "content": "I'm sorry to hear you need to send a rejection email, but I can certainly help you draft that while keeping the conversation light and professional. Here is a template you can use:\n\nSubject: Update on Your Application for Senior Developer Role\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you for taking the time to interview with us for the Senior Developer position in Austin. We were truly impressed by your strong system design skills and the excellent culture fit you demonstrated during our conversations.\n\nHowever, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with a candidate who has slightly more specific experience with our current cloud stack. We want to ensure we make the best decision for our team's immediate needs.\n\nWe truly appreciate your interest in our company and wish you the very best in your job search. Please feel free to reach out if you have any questions.\n\nWarm regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Title]\n\nI hope this draft helps you communicate your decision clearly and kindly. Let me know if you need any further adjustments!",
