      "content": "I can certainly help you add that warmth and keep the door open for the future while maintaining professionalism. Here is a revised version that incorporates your request to keep their info on file without sounding like a waste of time:\n\nSubject: Update on Your Application for Senior Developer Role\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you again for taking the time to interview with us for the Senior Developer position in Austin. We were genuinely impressed by your strong system design skills and the excellent culture fit you demonstrated during our conversations.\n\nHowever, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with a candidate who has slightly more specific experience with our current cloud stack. We want to ensure we make the best decision for our team's immediate needs.\n\nThat said, we truly appreciate your interest in our company and wish you the very best in your job search. We will keep your information on file and be sure to reach out if a future opening aligns better with your specific skillset. We hope to stay in touch, and we certainly don't want to burn this bridge.\n\nWarm regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Title]\n\nLet me know if you'd like to tweak the tone further!",
